articles.title: US tariffs are paid almost entirely by Americans, a German study finds
articles.content: A Kiel Institute study found US tariffs are mostly paid by American importers and consumers. The study found foreign exporters paid only around 4% of the tariff cost. The research contradicts Trump's messaging that Americans aren't paying for tariffs. A favorite tool of President Donald Trump has been costing Americans, according to new study.
